06180nam a22009135i 9783110914726DE-B159720230228015514.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20171997gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831109147267 a10.1515/97831109147262doi  a(DE-B1597)45595  a(OCoLC)1011440102  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh0481pa430qDE-10100aGerman: Syntactic Problems – Problematic Syntax /ced. by Werner Abraham, Elly van Gelderen.  aReprint 2017 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2017] 4c©1997  a1 online resource (VI, 323 p.) :bZahlr. Abb.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLinguistische Arbeiten ,x0344-6727 ;v37400tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction I -- tMinimalism: Why it is not 'the end of syntax' -- tThe base structure of the German clause under discourse functional weight: contentful functional categories vs. derivative functional categories -- tWord order in English: old problems and new answers -- tInflection and movement in Old English -- tProjective Economy -- tTransitive expletive constructions and the evidence supporting the Multiple Specifier Hypothesis -- tIntroduction II -- tThe Minimalist Program -- tToward a uniform account of scrambling and clitic doubling -- tPronouns and the left periphery of West Germanic embedded clauses -- tAgreement and case matching in noun phrases in German -- tDeriving conjoined XPs: a minimal deletion approach -- tIntroduction III -- tWord order and language acquisition – Kayne’s universal directionality restriction -- tThe Initial Hypothesis of syntax: A Minimalist perspective on language acquisition and attrition -- tThe acquisition of German and the “Initial Hypothesis of Syntax”: A reply to Platzack -- tAddresses of authors -- tGeneral index of subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Buch umfaßt elf Beiträge zur linguistischen Grammatik des Deutschen, des Englischen und der diachronischen Vorstufen des Englischen. Theoriehintergrund ist der Minimalismus von Chomsky (1993) sowie Weiterentwicklungen (Kayne 1993, Chomsky 1995), die allesamt sprachtypologische Vergleiche interessant machen. Ein Teil der Arbeiten ist kritisch gegenüber Teilen der Theorieansätze, die bei Universalanspruch der Beschreibung die besondere Faktenlage des Deutschen nicht berücksichtigen und ihr nicht gerecht werden können.  aThe volume assembles eleven articles presenting a linguistic approach to the grammar of German, English and the diachronic forerunners of English. Common to all is a theoretical discussion against the background of Chomskyan minimalism (1993) and more recent developments of it (Kayne 1993, Chomsky 1995), all of which make language typology comparisons an interesting proposition. Some of the articles are critical of certain aspects of these theoretical approaches. For all their claims to descriptive universality, it transpires that they fail to address a number of features specific to German.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEnglish languagexSyntax. 0aGerman languagexSyntax. 0aGermanic languagesxSyntax. 4aDeutsch. 4aEnglisch. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAbraham, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbraham, Werner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAlexiadou, Artemis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnagnostopoulou, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzepluch, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelderen, Elly van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula